Short description: Inclusive Storytimes support children and families with additional needs to foster early literacy skills through stories, songs and activities. This program is run in partnership with Denise Chan (Speech Pathologist, Beacon Allied Health, Carmen Szeto (Occupational Therapist) and April Sia (Play Therapist), and will provide engaging storytime and literacy activities, while also offering specialised support to address specific challenges and concerns unique to each family's situation. Each month will include a special theme around emotional needs, behaviours, movement and early language and literacy development, to empower parents and carers with knowledge and resources that will benefit their children long after the program ends.  NOTE: only runs on the last Friday of the month
Term dates: Not available in school holidays or public holidays

Short description:
Our exciting new sessions will bring children and parents together to develop the required language, number and motor skills to enable them to confidently adapt to the classroom environment.

'Get Ready for Big School' works in alignment with NSW Department of Education's transition to school guidelines. Grown-ups work with their child to learn and practice the skills needed to begin kindergarten and prepare them for classroom expectations. 

Bookings are required and must be made on the day of the program by calling the participating libraries from 9.30am onward.
Term dates: Not available in school holidays or public holidays
